\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'93Son of warlike Peleus,\uc0\u8232 you must hear this dreadful news\'97something\u8232 I wish weren\'92t so\'97Patroclus lies dead.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[20]\u8232 Men are fighting now around the body.\u8232 He\'92s stripped. Hector with his gleaming helmet\u8232 has the armour.\'94\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\
\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0Antilochus finished speaking.\uc0\u8232 A black cloud of grief swallowed up Achilles.\u8232 With both hands he scooped up soot and dust and poured it\u8232 on his head, covering his handsome face with dirt,\u8232 covering his sweet-smelling tunic with black ash.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a030\u8232 He lay sprawling\'97his mighty warrior\'92s massive body\u8232 collapsed and stretched out in the dust. With his hands,\u8232 he tugged at his own hair, disfiguring himself.\u8232 The women slaves acquired as battle trophies\u8232 by Achilles and Patroclus, hearts overwhelmed\u8232 with anguish, began to scream aloud. They rushed outside\u8232 and beat their breasts around warlike Achilles.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[30]\u8232 Then all the women\'92s legs gave way, and they fell down.\u8232 Across from them, Antilochus lamented,\u8232 eyes full of tears, as he held Achilles by the hand.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a040\u8232 Achilles\'92 noble heart moaned aloud. Antilochus\u8232 feared he might hurt himself or slit his throat\u8232 with his own sword. Achilles gave a huge cry of grief.\u8232 His noble mother heard it from the ocean depths\u8232 where she was sitting by her ancient father.\u8232 She began to wail. Then around her gathered\u8232 all the divine daughters of Nereus deep in the sea\'97\u8232 Glauce, Thaleia, Cymodoce, Nesaea,\u8232 Speio, Thoe, ox-eyed Hali\'eb, Cymotho\'eb,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a